description:
&lt;p&gt;GP Practices in Bath and North East Somerset, via the local GP Federation (BEMS), are seeking to recruit innovative, self-motivated and well-organised Nurse Associates. You will be a Qualified Nurse Associate registered with the NMC, with proven clinical and communication skills to join our professional and friendly multi-disciplinary teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This patient-facing role involves working within your scope of clinical practice, supported by supervision from a Senior Nurse, to provide a range of tasks within the Practice Nursing Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will benefit from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Joining an organisation that is judged by CQC to be excellently well led&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working within teams of highly performing GP practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to additional continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHS Pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post may involve travel between the PCN practices and other venues to help fulfil the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BEMS is a not-for-profit Community Mutual Provider, whose members include local GPs and practices as well as staff and patients. It supplies NHS services that are free to all Bath &amp; North East Somerset Patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicant will have access to the NHS Pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
